stylometry: Loggical upper limits show the boundaries and limits you have on certain numbers and quantities of your business. A logical upper limit is necessary to know so that you know your limits on your production quantities and resources available. Theres never an infinite amount of recources and tools you can use, and staff you can employ, and units you can produce. Therefore, it is pertinent that you understand how much of something you have to work with, and not succeed that number which would be detrimental to your business. It helps in models when using the solver because the solver will not find solutions using quantities for aspects that are higher than the number specified in the logical upper bounds.
